  "text": "Knee arthrodesis on the other hand stands out as a salvage procedure with better functional outcomes and patient satisfaction. In fact, a recent systematic review proved that arthrodesis is the procedure of choice, when compared to suppressive antibiotics, two-stage reimplantation and amputation, for management of persistent infection after a failed two-stage reimplantation procedure [CITATION_1] .",
